DENMARK: Danish August consumer confidence +6 (July +3).Danish August consumer confidence +6 (July +3).Denmark's consumer confidence indicator was +6 in August, up from +3 in July 1996, the National Statistics Office said on Tuesday.		   Aug 96	    July 96	  Aug 95			+6		 +3		  +11NOTE: The survey asks a cross section of Denmark's population its views on current personal and national economic trends, along with consumer intentions for coming months. Changes in consumer confidence are indicated by a higher or lower weighted rating, rather than by index.--Chris Follett, Copenhagen newsroom +45-33969650